transcript: I once worked for an actual witch, I think. She was never happy until she was setting one employee against another. This was at a big intellectual think tank, but she didn’t care. She had as much respect for experts and best-selling authors as she had for rats. I once heard an employee cry in her office as she laughed. I started to call her Baba Yaga, which caught on at the office, because people didn’t know who Baba Yaga was. For the uninitiated, Baba Yaga is a swamp witch of Eastern European legend who lives in a hut that stands on chicken legs. Baba Yaga, I miss ya, ya crazy old bat.
